Elmsley remarks that Medea’s next words show that the place of butial she had selected was out of the territory of Corinth, and then quotes Livy, xxxii. 23, “ Promon- torium est adversus Sicyonem, J unonis quam vocant Acraeam, in altum excurrens: trajectus inde Corinthum, septem millia ferme passuum.”

1396. μένε καὶ γῆρας. This is a ferocious speech of Medea's. “ Wait till you are an old man. Then you will find out what loneliness is.” So Coriolanus is said to have declared that no one could tell all the bitterness of exile, till old age fell upon him.
